FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,FThe couple, from Sussex, are being
OL,7,Fheld in Tehran's Evin Prison after
OL,8,Fthey were detained and sentenced on
OL,9,Fcharges of espionage, which they deny.
OL,11,FThe Foreign Office have described the
OL,12,Fjail sentences the pair received as
OL,13,F"completely appalling and totally
OL,14,Funjustifiable" ` saying their welfare
OL,15,Fis a "priority" for the Government.
OL,17,FIn a statement, Mr Foreman called on
OL,18,Fthe Government to "step out of the
OL,19,Fshadows and help us".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,FHe said: "We are both currently
OL,7,Fserving 14 months into a 10-year
OL,8,Fprison sentence in Evin Prison,
OL,9,FTehran, for crimes that were never
OL,10,Fcommitted; spying for the UK and
OL,11,FIsrael.
OL,13,F"We were charged based on falsified
OL,14,Fevidence that was fabricated to suit
OL,15,Fthe maximum sentence.
OL,17,F"Our Government are fully aware of
OL,18,Fthis information and know we are 100%
OL,19,Finnocent.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,F"We are proud to be British, but by
OL,7,Fnow we feel let down, alone, and
OL,8,Fcompletely frustrated by the lack of
OL,9,Fpublic defence by the people in charge
OL,10,Fof the Government."
OL,12,FHe continued: "It's very difficult to
OL,13,Funderstand why our innocence has not
OL,14,Fbeen said publicly. We are not spies.
OL,15,FThe charges against us are simply not
OL,16,Ftrue.
OL,18,F"I am asking you, Sir Keir Starmer,
OL,19,FYvette Cooper, Hamish Falconer and
OL,20,FHugo Shorter, you know we are innocent.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,F"Go public with the information ` you
OL,7,Fhave to clearly step up, step out of
OL,8,Fthe shadows and help us. Our lives are
OL,9,Fconstantly at risk.
OL,11,F"We are now in a prison in a war zone.
OL,12,FWe have gone from a challenging
OL,13,Fsituation to a life-threatening
OL,14,Fsituation.
OL,16,F"You have chosen to give us zero
OL,17,Finformation on what's happening to us,
OL,18,Fwhat to do and where to go if the
OL,19,Fprison doors were to open.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,F"There is a serious lack of commitment
OL,7,Ffor our safety."
OL,9,FMr Foreman's statement added: "Lastly,
OL,10,Fwe would like to say a massive thank
OL,11,Fyou to our families and friends who
OL,12,Fhave been... and are still the driving
OL,13,Fforce and the backbone fighting for
OL,14,Four release and our safe passage back
OL,15,Fhome."
OL,17,FMs Foreman's son, Joe Bennett, said
OL,18,Fhis mother is "in pieces" ` calling
OL,19,Ftheir detention a "slow-motion
OL,20,Fdestruction".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,FHe said: "My mum is in pieces. She's
OL,7,Fgone from always finding the positive
OL,8,Fto feeling completely lost.
OL,10,F"The sense that she's been abandoned
OL,11,Fby her own Government is breaking her."
OL,13,F"They are not spies, and our
OL,14,FGovernment knows that. They do not
OL,15,Fbelieve these charges.
OL,17,F"They need to say so publicly.
OL,18,FAnything less only helps sustain a
OL,19,Ffalse narrative and prolongs the
OL,20,Fsuffering of innocent people."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,F"They are being held in appalling
OL,7,Fconditions; sleeping on metal bunks
OL,8,Fwithout mattresses, in constant pain.
OL,9,FCraig is in agony with an untreated
OL,10,Fdental abscess.
OL,12,F"They have nowhere to turn. This isn't
OL,13,Fjust detention, it's slow-motion
OL,14,Fdestruction."
OL,16,FThe Foreign, Commonwealth and
OL,17,FDevelopment Office (FCDO) warns all
OL,18,FBritish and British-Iranian nationals
OL,19,Fnot to travel to Iran because of a
OL,20,F"significant risk of arrest,
OL,21,Fquestioning or detention".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774293066
OL,3,CBritish man jailed in Iran criticises
OL,4,CGovernment for abandonment in war zone
OL,6,FIn a statement, a spokesperson for the
OL,7,FFCDO said: "The welfare of British
OL,8,Fnationals detained in Iran is a
OL,9,Fpriority for this government and
OL,10,Fcontinues to be during the current
OL,11,Fsituation in the Middle East. Craig
OL,12,Fand Lindsay's sentences are completely
OL,13,Fappalling and totally unjustifiable.
OL,15,F"We will continue to pursue this case
OL,16,Frelentlessly with the Iranian regime
OL,17,Funtil we see Craig and Lindsay safely
OL,18,Freturned to the UK and reunited with
OL,19,Ftheir family.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
